Head surface matte, with strong and dense isodiametric microsculpture, with fine punctation, distance between punctures equals 1­2 times their diameter. Frons with sparser punctation, in both sexes with longitudinal impression. Temple length to eye length ratio 1.0­ 1.2 . Antennal article 2 is 1.1 times as long as article 3 , articles 4­5 slightly elongate (length to width ratio 1.2­1.3 ), articles 6­7 as long as wide, articles 8­10 slightly transverse (length to width ratio 0.8 ) (
Fig. 18
).

Posterior margin of male tergum 8 with four blunt projections, emarginate medially (
Fig. 19
).

Distribution. Known from the Pacific coast of North America , from Alaska to California (
Fig. 52
).
